ege and Anxiety explores how these tensions play out in three areas: consumption and lifestyle, residential differentiation, and education. In all three areas, the dominant orientation of the affluent middle class is to preserve their newfound privilege and pass it onto their children, causing much disaffection and anxiety to the less fortunate members.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aIncome distributionxSocial aspectszKorea. 0aMiddle classzKoreaxEconomic conditionsy20th century. 0aMiddle classzKoreaxEconomic conditionsy21st century. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aSociology & Social Science. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Korea.2bisacsh  agangnam style of status competition and class making, globalization and the middle class, new affluent and privileged segment within the middle class, middle class in east asia, Gangnam middle class.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501764936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501764936/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099296-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter